      "writtenOn": "2021-06-14T15:37:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If these ClipCmds represent intersect operations, the zbuffer needs to have drawZ written to every pixel NOT inside fRect, since clip is meant to rasterize to the pixels that cannot be drawn to. If it\u0027s a difference op, then we just rasterize the rect itself.\n\nMy doc talked about limiting the rasterization of intersect clip ops the bounds of the shape because it could rely on the scissor test to clip out everything outside the bounds of the shape. Since we don\u0027t have a scissor in this particular case, we should do (everything - rect) directly. And since the clips are limited to integer rects, it would just always be the scissor and then we wouldn\u0027t actually be testing the fundamental theory of the clip sorting.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 195,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 201,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "30d81895e1110a8280ee2c5359cfdd2f0692bf5a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9eacad5d_dabe3418",
        "filename": "experimental/ngatoy/Cmds.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 201,
